    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-02T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-02T06:00:00-05:00" n="241"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d241">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1159</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Cairo</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_AO1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Arnold</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Cairo</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-02T13:00:00+02:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">November 2, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10:55 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>British Chargé d’Affaires just notified me that General commanding British Army
                    occupation in Egypt has been ordered by British Government to assume military
                    control and protection of Egypt and that martial law will be proclaimed here
                    to-day and that the Government of Great Britain will not assume responsibility
                    for any person disobeying orders of the General.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AO1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Arnold</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
